parameters: \pop[185]Welcome to the first of four \C[23]Fragment Maps\c[0].
\pop[185]This is how you will navigate through your personal experience.
\pop[19]The top row is made up of \C[23]Pivotal Fragments\c[0].
\pop[19]You must complete all six, but can complete them in any order.
\pop[153]Upon completing all six, you can interact with this arrow to move forward.
\pop[153]You will witness a culmination of this \c[23]Fragment Map\c[0], before moving on to the next.
\pop[91]This second row consists of personal \C[23]Heart-to-Heart Fragments\c[0].
\pop[91]These are optional, but highly recommended, as they are the key to forming bonds and relationships.
\pop[91]Right now, you only have access to Isaac and Dante. But that will change in the next \c[23]Fragment Map\c[0].
\pop[172]These are skits based on exchanges made in your group's chatroom.
\pop[172]For your benefit, they will be portrayed just like any other \c[23]Fragment\c[0].
\pop[186]Upon completing a \c[23]Pivotal Fragment\c[0], you will unlock a journal entry.
\pop[186]These explore Delta's personal thoughts as events slowly unfold.
\pop[186]There will be five to unlock in each \c[23]Fragment Map\c[0]; and they unlock in a predetermined order.
\pop[187]Should you wish, you can also toggle the Nostalgia Filter.
\pop[187]This will apply a vintage look to your experience.
\pop[185]You are now ready to continue your journey unhindered.
\pop[185]Checkmarks will appear beside completed \c[23]Fragments\c[0], so you can monitor your progress.
\pop[185]It is also recommended that you alternate between various \c[23]Fragment \c[0]types.
\pop[185]Enjoy, and make it an experience to remember.
